public abstract class Structure extends Object
The Structure class serves as an abstract base class for various structures used in Moera Node API.

  • Method Details

    • getExtra

      public Object getExtra()
      Retrieves the additional data associated with the structure. This data is not present in the serialized JSON form of the structure.
      Returns:
      the extra object stored in the structure, or null if no extra data is set

    • getOrCreateExtra

      public <T> T getOrCreateExtra(Supplier<T> creator)
      Retrieves the existing extra data associated with the structure or, if it does not exist, creates and assigns new extra data using the provided creator.

      This method can be conveniently used for keeping complex objects in the extra property. For example, if an object of StructureExtras class should be kept in extra, it can be accessed as follows: 

           structure.getOrCreateExtra(StructureExtras::new).getSomething()
      getOrCreateExtra method ensures that the object will always be present.
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the extra data
      Parameters:
      creator - a supplier function used to create the extra data if it does not already exist
      Returns:
      the existing or newly created extra data of type T

    • setExtra

      public void setExtra(Object extra)
      Sets additional data associated with the structure. This data is not included in the serialized JSON form of the structure and can be used to store custom information.
      Parameters:
      extra - the extra object to be associated with the structure

    • validate

      public void validate()
      Validates the structure.

      If the structure contains incorrect data, this method should throw ValidationFailure exception.
